00:37:55.930 --> 00:38:00.930
Alicia, I've been chatting for a
while, just what would you like

00:38:00.930 --> 00:38:04.920
to share with folks walk watching
in terms of their journey

00:38:04.920 --> 00:38:08.100
as developers in terms
of the work they do

00:38:08.100 --> 00:38:11.050
in terms of making it accessible,
or what's the best way

00:38:11.050 --> 00:38:13.220
that you would, or what
advice would you give to them?

00:38:14.620 --> 00:38:15.620
<v Alicia> Oh, okay.

00:38:16.720 --> 00:38:19.110
It's fun to learn this stuff.

00:38:19.110 --> 00:38:20.570
It is really fun.

00:38:20.570 --> 00:38:22.367
At first,
it seems really overwhelming

00:38:22.367 --> 00:38:26.160
and you just have to start
where you are.

00:38:26.160 --> 00:38:28.440
A lot of times it's Googling.

00:38:30.120 --> 00:38:34.934
The most important thing
is to actually witness

00:38:34.935 --> 00:38:38.337
or find documentation
or demonstrations

00:38:38.338 --> 00:38:41.910
of people with
disabilities using the web

00:38:41.910 --> 00:38:45.680
and how they use their assisted
technology because then you start

00:38:45.680 --> 00:38:52.430
to think from the technology's
viewpoint because this has been said

00:38:52.430 --> 00:38:54.750
in some of the other sessions.

00:38:54.750 --> 00:38:56.900
A lot of times people will just
have, "Read more.

00:38:56.900 --> 00:38:57.570
Read more.

00:38:57.570 --> 00:38:59.260
Click here for links."

00:39:01.350 --> 00:39:04.580
With some assisted technologies,
they pull the links out

00:39:04.580 --> 00:39:07.550
and just put them on the sidebar
so they can just scan those.

00:39:07.550 --> 00:39:11.620
If you don't have more
than click here, read more,

00:39:11.620 --> 00:39:13.870
then they have no idea
what the context is.

00:39:13.870 --> 00:39:19.320
Actually, you put more context
around every piece of the site,

00:39:19.320 --> 00:39:23.561
every piece of the layout,
or the piece of this feature

00:39:23.561 --> 00:39:24.230
that's going in.

00:39:24.230 --> 00:39:25.810
What if this stood alone?

00:39:27.580 --> 00:39:32.760
I can't even remember,
but there was a situation--

00:39:32.760 --> 00:39:36.680
Oh, it was just organizing
some Dropbox folders.

00:39:36.680 --> 00:39:38.490
It comes into everything.

00:39:38.490 --> 00:39:41.080
We were organizing them by
year, but inside each folder,

00:39:41.080 --> 00:39:44.250
we used the same titles that
we'd have used in other years.

00:39:44.250 --> 00:39:47.080
I said, "No, what if one of
those folders is separate

00:39:47.080 --> 00:39:50.230
without the context
of its parent folder?

00:39:50.230 --> 00:39:53.850
Let's put the year in front of
every folder in the folder too."

00:39:55.560 --> 00:39:57.610
Your whole world
starts to change like,

00:39:57.610 --> 00:40:06.710
"We can make this better
organized for everybody."

00:40:06.710 --> 00:40:11.150
Also, there's an edX course that
I would suggest that everyone

00:40:13.750 --> 00:40:17.050
just checks that out because
like what has also been said

00:40:17.050 --> 00:40:19.370
in a lot of sessions is a
lot of us thought it was just

00:40:19.370 --> 00:40:22.180
for blind people that we
were doing this accessibility

00:40:22.180 --> 00:40:28.230
but that's probably, 1 out of 50
different disabilities that are

00:40:28.230 --> 00:40:29.490
being affected by the internet.

00:40:29.490 --> 00:40:30.490
[laughs]

00:40:30.820 --> 00:40:34.660
That course, the edX
course, is really good.

00:40:34.660 --> 00:40:39.510
I guess Joe will supply
that resource link.

00:40:39.510 --> 00:40:41.580
<v Joe> The other story
and it just came to mind

00:40:41.580 --> 00:40:45.100
while you were talking, and for
the folks that are out there,

00:40:45.100 --> 00:40:51.140
our group, we have our own
Slack channel, and we share wins

00:40:51.140 --> 00:40:52.810
with each other.

