00:40:57.210 --> 00:40:58.900
<v Alicia> Yes,
that was another one.

00:40:58.900 --> 00:41:01.600
I was noticing that I couldn't
tap to the submit button.

00:41:01.600 --> 00:41:04.560
I was like, "Oh, that's bad."

00:41:04.560 --> 00:41:10.450
Then I told them about it, and
the support girl wrote back to me,

00:41:10.450 --> 00:41:12.690
"I'm sending this
straight to the top.

00:41:12.690 --> 00:41:14.580
It's got attention ASAP on it."

00:41:14.580 --> 00:41:16.320
I'm like, "Oh, cool."

00:41:16.320 --> 00:41:18.776
I just tested it again and
it seems to be working.

00:41:19.632 --> 00:41:20.112
<v Joe> Awesome.

00:41:20.112 --> 00:41:22.013
<v Alicia> [crosstalk]

00:41:22.013 --> 00:41:23.120
ActiveCampaign.

00:41:23.120 --> 00:41:26.120
<v Joe> You can make an impact just
by reaching out to these folks.

00:41:26.120 --> 00:41:29.130
I think one thing that's really
powerful about what you were talking

00:41:29.130 --> 00:41:32.880
about today is that these
people want to make changes,

00:41:32.880 --> 00:41:35.920
but they may not know that they
need to so by you reaching out,

00:41:35.920 --> 00:41:38.130
you're that conduit
to make it happen.

00:41:38.130 --> 00:41:39.950
For the group,
I wanted to toss this one out.

00:41:39.950 --> 00:41:41.030
What's next?

