At this point, anyone could
jump in and just [crosstalk].

00:41:52.250 --> 00:41:54.090
<v Alicia> I'll just
be really quick.

00:41:54.090 --> 00:41:55.580
Exposure.

00:41:55.580 --> 00:42:00.390
You don't have to know the code or
tech stuff, but, if you can write

00:42:00.390 --> 00:42:03.080
or if you have a blog,
just tell a story.

00:42:03.080 --> 00:42:05.210
A story about someone you know
trying to use the internet

00:42:06.690 --> 00:42:11.760
and have them talk about it or
write about how you discovered

00:42:11.760 --> 00:42:16.030
how to use ARIA label "polite"
so the slider goes through

00:42:16.030 --> 00:42:18.410
and it doesn't interrupt
someone in the screen reader

00:42:18.410 --> 00:42:20.080
while reading another
part of the site.

00:42:20.080 --> 00:42:22.550
Just anything that you know
about accessibility, make it fun

00:42:22.550 --> 00:42:24.880
and knowledgeable so that
it starts to be a thing

00:42:24.880 --> 00:42:26.700
that people run across
almost all the time.

00:42:28.710 --> 00:42:29.460
<v Joe> Sally?

00:42:29.460 --> 00:42:30.281
Ron?

00:42:32.261 --> 00:42:38.170
<v Ron> I could just encourage any
developers to wake up about this.

00:42:38.170 --> 00:42:43.040
It's something I wasn't focused on
at all for-- I've been doing this

00:42:43.040 --> 00:42:45.540
for maybe 23 years or so, 24 years.

00:42:47.130 --> 00:42:56.020
I put in text in all my images but
I was doing it completely wrong

00:42:56.020 --> 00:42:59.630
and out of ignorance and probably
for SEO as much as anything else.

00:43:02.340 --> 00:43:05.140
It's really, really important
and it's really, really dumb.

00:43:05.140 --> 00:43:08.900
It's just dumb not
to go this route.

00:43:08.900 --> 00:43:10.670
You're missing.

00:43:10.670 --> 00:43:18.160
You're excluding a huge swath of all
possible viewers of your material.

00:43:18.160 --> 00:43:23.930
For those with e-commerce
sites, you're excluding gigantic

00:43:23.930 --> 00:43:24.950
commercial opportunity.

00:43:26.710 --> 00:43:29.500
This work raises all boats.

00:43:29.500 --> 00:43:30.800
It's been shown.

00:43:30.800 --> 00:43:34.190
This is something in
Sumner's presentations.

00:43:34.190 --> 00:43:38.670
She shows you the curb cuts
and streets that were once

00:43:38.670 --> 00:43:44.390
just for wheelchair folks that
help all of us and there are many,

00:43:44.390 --> 00:43:47.140
many examples like that.

00:43:47.140 --> 00:43:54.030
It's completely insane that 90%
of websites do not help people

00:43:54.030 --> 00:43:55.030
with disabilities.

00:43:56.580 --> 00:44:01.080
At the same time, the list of
people with disabilities is growing.

00:44:02.690 --> 00:44:03.690
It's completely crazy.

00:44:05.170 --> 00:44:08.040
We just have to get to
work and we need to talk.

00:44:08.040 --> 00:44:11.260
Like Alicia said, we need to share.

00:44:11.260 --> 00:44:17.870
We who are doing it, need to talk
about it and share the techniques.

